<dl id="n03009a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03009a">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03009a"> 9(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>4 yrs<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> / Tours (S. Martin) <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">6</span></span> / <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>14 years<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> / S Germain Auxerrois</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> After six years&apos; captivity Patrick escaped from Ireland to France and made his way to <mark>Tours</mark>, where he stayed for <mark>four years</mark> receiving instructions from <mark>St. Martin</mark>. Then he spent about <mark>fourteen years with St. Germanus of Auxerre</mark>, who sent him to Pope Celestine to receive the episcopacy. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 11</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Continued from previous page. St Germain l&apos;Auxerrois is also the famous Paris church whose bell was the signal for the Massacre of St Bartholomew. </mm> </dd></dl>
